We’re going to put Figure code into the second column here to get us a photo and caption, but I don’t want you to pull the example code from Bootstrap Documentation because I need to explain how some of it works and that is easier if we build it up ourselves.

Replace the text “Column 2” with the following code:
&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
  &lt;img src="img/gutenberg.jpeg" class="figure-img" alt="Guetenberg Bible"&gt;
  &lt;figcaption class="figure-caption"&gt;A caption for the above image.&lt;/figcaption&gt;
